def multiplcation_tabel(n):
    table = []
    for i in range(1, n + 1):
        row = []
        for j in range(1, n + 1):
            row.append(i * j)
        table.append(row)
    return table
For every row i from 1 to n, the inner loop multiplies i by each j and appends the product, building one row at a time.
